    <h1>Privacy Statement</h1>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>Welcome to did ("we," "our," "us"). We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Statement explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our timesheet and calendar integration service (the "Service").</p>
        <p>This Privacy Statement applies to information we collect when you use our Service, including through subscriptions managed by your organization.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>2.1 User Data</h3>
        <p>When you access the Service through your organization's subscription, we collect certain information about you, which may include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Identity information (name, email address, user ID)</li>
            <li>Professional information (job title, department, manager)</li>
            <li>Contact information (email address, phone number)</li>
            <li>Authentication data (provider tokens for calendar access)</li>
            <li>User preferences and configuration settings</li>
            <li>Profile images (if enabled in subscription settings)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>2.2 Calendar Data</h3>
        <p>The Service integrates with your calendar (Microsoft Outlook, Google Calendar) to retrieve event data, which may include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Event titles, descriptions, and categories</li>
            <li>Event timing (start and end time, duration)</li>
            <li>Event participants</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We exclude calendar events marked as "private" from our processing.</p>
        
        <h3>2.3 Timesheet Data</h3>
        <p>We collect data about your time entries, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Projects and tasks you work on</li>
            <li>Time spent on various activities</li>
            <li>Submitted and forecasted hours</li>
            <li>Vacation and absence records</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the collected information for various purposes, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Providing and maintaining the Service</li>
            <li>Generating timesheet reports and analytics</li>
            <li>Processing time entries for project tracking</li>
            <li>Managing vacation and absence records</li>
            <li>Enabling collaboration within your organization</li>
            <li>Sending notifications about timesheet submissions (if enabled)</li>
            <li>Improving and optimizing the Service</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>4. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>We may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>With other members of your organization according to the roles and permissions framework</li>
            <li>With authorized third-party service providers who perform services on our behalf</li>
            <li>When required by law or to protect our rights</li>
        </ul>
        <p>If your organization has enabled external user invitations, limited information may be shared with external collaborators according to the security settings configured by your subscription administrator.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate security measures to protect your personal information, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Secure authentication through Microsoft Entra ID or other identity providers</li>
            <li>Role-based access controls</li>
            <li>Data encryption in transit and at rest</li>
            <li>Regular security assessments</li>
            <li>Security group membership validation (if enabled)</li>
            <li>Domain restriction capabilities for organization-wide security</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to provide you with the Service and as required by applicable laws. When your organization terminates its subscription or you are removed as a user, we retain data according to our data retention policies or as required by law.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>7. Third-Party Integrations</h2>
        <p>Our Service integrates with various third-party services:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Microsoft Graph API for calendar and user data</li>
            <li>Microsoft Teams for notifications (if enabled)</li>
            <li>Google Calendar API (if enabled)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Data shared with these services is subject to their respective privacy policies.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>8. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
        <p>Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information, such as:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access to your personal information</li>
            <li>Rectification of inaccurate information</li>
            <li>Erasure of your personal information</li>
            <li>Restriction of processing of your personal information</li>
            <li>Data portability</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, please contact your organization's subscription administrator.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>The Service is not intended for use by children under 16 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 16.</p>
